article.headline: Bailey has 18, Wofford downs Middle Tennessee 74-64 in OT
article.description: — Dillon Bailey's 18 points helped Wofford defeat Middle Tennessee 74-64 in overtime on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Bailey has 18, Wofford downs Middle Tennessee 74-64 in OT
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. -- — Dillon Bailey's 18 points helped Wofford defeat Middle Tennessee 74-64 in overtime on Saturday night. Bailey shot 7 for 13 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free-throw line for the Terriers (3-5). Corey Tripp scored 17 points and added 10 rebounds and seven assists. Kyler Filewich had 15 points and shot 7 of 12 from the field and 1 for 4 from the foul line. The Terriers stopped a five-game slide with the win. The Blue Raiders (4-5) were led by Jestin Porter, who recorded 15 points. Justin Bufford added 13 points and four assists for Middle Tennessee. Jalen Jordan also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
